{"abstract": "Background: Evaluation of the quality of research software is a challenging and relevant issue, still not sufficiently addressed by the scientific community. Methods: Our contribution begins by defining, precisely but widely enough, the notions of research software and of its authors followed by a study of the evaluation issues, as the basis for the proposition of a sound assessment protocol: the CDUR procedure. Results: CDUR comprises four steps introduced as follows: Citation, to deal with correct RS identification, Dissemination, to measure good dissemination practices, Use, devoted to the evaluation of usability aspects, and Research, to assess the impact of the scientific work. Conclusions: Some conclusions and recommendations are finally included. The evaluation of research is the keystone to boost the evolution of the Open Science policies and practices. \u00a0It is as well our belief that research software evaluation is a fundamental step to induce better research software practices and, thus, a step towards more efficient science.", "arxivId": null, "authors": [{"authorId": "1403733922", "name": "Teresa Gomez-Diaz", "url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1403733922"}, {"authorId": "1711432", "name": "T. Recio", "url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1711432"}], "citationVelocity": 0, "citations": [{"arxivId": null, "authors": [{"authorId": "1780710", "name": "H. Anzt", "url": null}, {"authorId": "1879212186", "name": "Felix Bach", "url": null}, {"authorId": "2422392", "name": "Stephan Druskat", "url": null}, {"authorId": "46785695", "name": "F. Loeffler", "url": null}, {"authorId": "3201248", "name": "A. Loewe", "url": null}, {"authorId": "3322837", "name": "B. Renard", "url": null}, {"authorId": "1721433", "name": "G. Seemann", "url": null}, {"authorId": "48780118", "name": "A. Struck", "url": null}, {"authorId": "1667848596", "name": "Elke Achhammer", "url": null}, {"authorId": "147764420", "name": "Piush Aggarwal", "url": nu